msgctxt "talk000"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Good morning! Welcome to\n"
"<2.se_co>Tabantha Bridge Stable<3.re_co>, home of the\n"
"cutest white goats in all of Hyrule."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk001"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hello! And welcome to\n"
"<2.se_co>Tabantha Bridge Stable<3.re_co>, where I'm busy\n"
"cataloging some very important cargo."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk002"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Yes, welcome to <2.se_co>Tabantha Bridge Stable<3.re_co>,\n"
"where caring for the horses is the most\n"
"pressing matter on my plate."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk003"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to <2.se_co>Tabantha Bridge Stable<3.re_co>,\n"
"where looking at a child's sleeping face\n"
"makes me happy!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk004"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to <2.se_co>Tabantha Bridge Stable<3.re_co>,\n"
"where it's raining nonstop."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk005"
msgid "<1.so>Welcome to <2.se_co>Tabantha Bridge Stable<3.re_co>!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk100"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you need directions, just ask me.\n"
"Any direction you want to know about?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: sound
msgctxt "talk101"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The east, huh?\n"
"The east...\n"
"Yeah...\n"
"<2.so>My aunt always tells me I should travel\n"
"all over while I'm still young...\n"
"\n"
"But that <3.se_co>Ludfo's Bog <4.re_co>isn't a place\n"
"anyone should travel to in my opinion.\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>It's had a constant cover of black storm\n"
"clouds since long before my aunt was\n"
"born.\n"
"If you ask me, it's a sign from Hylia\n"
"herself telling us not to go there.\n"
"And I don't want to make Hylia angry..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
#. 5: sound
msgctxt "talk102"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Well, to the east there's...<2.se_co>Ludfo's Bog<3.re_co>.\n"
"Funny story, actually.\n"
"\n"
"There used to be a constant cover of \n"
"dark storm clouds that had been there\n"
"long before even my aunt was born.\n"
"<4.so>But then they suddenly all vanished!\n"
"Praise Hylia!\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>I'm even thinking of taking the horses\n"
"there on a field trip soon."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: set_colour (blue)
#. 7: reset_colour
#. 8: sound
msgctxt "talk111"
msgid ""
"<1.so>South, huh? My aunt used to tell us\n"
"some crazy stories about that area.\n"
"\n"
"About how past <2.se_co>Tamio River<3.re_co>, on\n"
"<4.se_co>Satori Mountain<5.re_co>, there lived a <6.se_co>lord<7.re_co>\n"
"with dominion over all living things...\n"
"<8.so>It's an old legend that she tells the\n"
"children before bedtime, even today.\n"
"\n"
"She also tells them about \"the god who\n"
"watches over the stables.\"\n"
"Pfft..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk121"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Ah, the west...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"If you head west, you'll spot the\n"
"namesake of our stable, the\n"
"<2.se_co>Tabantha Great Bridge<3.re_co>.\n"
"If you cross the bridge and follow the\n"
"road, you'll eventually get to<4.se_co> Rito Village<5.re_co>,\n"
"where the Rito people live.\n"
"It's a REALLY long walk to Rito Village,\n"
"though, so you'll definitely want to bring\n"
"some snacks."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
msgctxt "talk122"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But...have you seen that THING?\n"
"That...that <2.se_co>creepy bird in the sky<3.re_co>?\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>It suddenly appeared above Rito Village\n"
"and won't go away. \n"
"\n"
"If you're going there, you should be\n"
"careful. Who knows what's going on\n"
"there."
msgstr ""

#. 1: choice
msgctxt "talk131"
msgid "Really? Well, be careful.<1.ch>"
msgstr ""

